Comment: EnvelopeType defines an extent using a pair of positions defining opposite corners in arbitrary dimensions. Here, the lower left corner point and upper right corner point are used.
A geomtrical object which has a Land Use Code (LUcode).
The lowermost vertex of the EnvelopeType.
The uppermost vertex of the EnvelopeType.
Specifies the coordinate system which the EnvelopeType refers to.
Specifies the number of dimensions which the EnvelopeType has.
An identifier unique within the EnvelopeType which refers to a specific CropMap.

A CROMEID is assigned as specified by the Rural Payments Agency (RPA) for a CropMap. The CROMEID is the unique identifier assigned to each CropMap, consisting of the letters RPA and a twelve digit number, which are the Easting and Northing coordinates of the centroid of the cell. For example a CropMap with CROMEID RPAXXXXXXYYYYYY would have a centre point with Easting XXXXXX and Northing YYYYYY.
Area is the quantity that expresses the extent of a two-dimensional region, shape, or planar lamina, in the plane. This value refers to the area of the CropMap in metres squared.
Length is a measure of distance. This value refers to the perimeter of the CropMap in metres.

The reference date is the date or date range of the images referenced to assign the Land Use Code to the CROME CropMap. The date format used is YYYYMMDD e.g. 20181121. The value is expected to remain constant for each CropMap in a CROME release.
Relates a CropMap to its vertex coordinates.
Centre point of a CropMap as identified by the Rural Payments Agency.
Specifies which EnvelopType the CropMap belongs to.
Specifies which Land Use Code (LUcode) is assigned to this CropMap.
